We recently launched Mexico Residency program at Plan B passport.
The process takes about 1-2 months due to lack of appointments in some cities/countries, but can be done much faster. 
Doesn't require investment - just proof of savings ($45 000) or salary (~$2500/month)

Cons: 
- NOT a travel document, therefor won't work for a scenario when your passport is revoked
- Needs renewal (usually annually)
- Sometimes comes with requirements for time spent in the country

Pros: 
- inexpensive
- easier paperwork
- quick to obtain
- allowed for those for whole dual citizenship is prohibited
- can be turned into a citizenship later if certain criteria are met

A temporary residence allows you to officially live, work and perform activities such as opening a bank account, obtaining driver license, opening an account on an exchange as a local.
A residence is NOT a travel document but rather a special status for a foreigner in a country.

Temporary residence - pros and cons /THREAD

Plan B residencies aren't as strong as Plan B passports, but can be very valuable in certain scenarios.

20/ The judge was very nice to me, asked me questions and advised never ever do it again. Later I found out the worst case scenario could be 30 days in jail and $5k. I am flying to Puerto Rico on Sunday so thanks for not throwing me in a cage.
19/ Around 4 pm, apparently one of Craigâ€™s representatives read my tweets and reported to the judge. After another break I was invited back to the court room for a, â€œtalk.â€ #russianspy

18/ I was trying to set aside my opinion on the whole story, and interpret the cross-examination how the judge (or others) might see it. Even so, even the interns expressed an unmistakeable level of incredulity.

17/ There were many companies mentioned, one wrapped up into another and co-owned through multisigs.  I wish they just had a whiteboard to draw it all out. Perhaps starting with, Tulip Limited, or Coin LTD, (sic).
16/ The hearing continued despite the expiration of official court house hours. None of the witnesses had time to participate today. There will be another hearing scheduled soon.
15/ Apparently, IF David set up the time release the way CSW and David discussed, he is supposed to gain access to another key in Jan or Dec 2020.
14/ Side note: I really felt bad for the stenographer, when they were going through tech staff. It was hilarious when he asked how to spell @GitHub

13/ So the document demand in court, is supposedly under control of 15 keys. It requires 8 out of 15 to decrypt, AND in a particular order. I still couldnâ€™t  ascertain how many keys he personally has exactly â€¦ maybe â€¦ seven?
12/ It became clear to me that - someone tried to falsify email metadata - but after changing the DATE (day, months and year) of the email, *they forgot to change what day of the week it was.*

11/ Cross-examination was a bomb! I was very impressed with ability of the lawyer to go through lines of code with a great confidence. Calling falsified emails and other documents by providing data from servers.

10/ The most emotional moment was when CSW was asked why he left bitcoin and decided to disassociate with Satoshiâ€™s pseudonym. â€œI was ashamed of my invention. They used it for child porn and hard drugs. I didnâ€™t want to be a part of it so I left. I even stopped being a pastor.â€
9/ After that we went on a long side track of agreeing what is a public address and what it stands for, in the community

8/ CSW and his lawyer: Are you satoshi? -Yes. Do you recognize this White Paper? -Yes. If you had a chance to provide the BTC addresses, would you? -Public Address is not an existing thing on Bitcoin network.
7/ Now back to todayâ€™s trial. CSW was supposed to present public addresses of the funds held in BTC he acquired before the end of 2013 but he still hasnâ€™t done it.
6/ Later it seem to appear that David actually owned 100% of W&K which supposed to have about a million of BTC from mining. Ira demanded to return these funds but it hasnâ€™t been done.

5/ CSW promised big money to Davidâ€™s family as part of his alleged ownership in W&K, and tried to keep it not public when Ira required an explanation on money transfers from W&K to CSW without notifying Kleimanâ€™s family.

4/ TLDR of the pre-story. 
According to the story: CSW created Bitcoin. Short after that he started working together with David Kleiman. By August 2010 they mined a ton of coins. David started a UK company W&K. David died in April 2013. Currently Ira Kleiman is Davidâ€™s heir.
